---
title: Sweet Chili Pork & Green Bean Bowls with Crispy Onions & Cilantro
description: Good news, friends: The path to sweet-and-savory dinner bliss is only 20 minutes away! In this recipe, pork and green beans are coated in a sumptuous sweet chili sauce, then topped with fresh cilantro and crispy fried onions. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy rice. The results? A symphony of flavors and textures so delicious, you might just lick the plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-chili-pork-green-bean-bowls-101f6e87.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-chili-pork-green-bean-bowls-5fd913fd4083e0249b5ad5e3-f2dcba32.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-chili-pork-green-bean-bowls-5fd913fd4083e0249b5ad5e3
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 20 minutes
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 930 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 99 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1280 mg
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch-long pieces. Quarter @lime{1}. Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, without stirring, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until pork is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

While pork cooks, add green beans and a splash of water to a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small pot with a splash of water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Carefully drain any excess water.

To pan with pork, stir in cooked green beans, @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until pork mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{} and top with pork mixture. Sprinkle with @crispy fried onions{1}(chopped) and chopped cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.